  "title": "cleaning supervisor ( Part time ) / Auditor",
  "description": "<p><strong>a)  Environmental Quality Audit, that comprises of:</strong></p><p>i. 100% of the following inspection units: entrance and\nlobby, lift cars, planter boxes and containers, porches, pavement, aprons,\nsidewalks, external game courts, carpark, driveway, hard standing, loading and\nunloading bay, field, gardens, side tables, bin centre / bin chute. </p><p>ii. 50% of the following inspection units: classrooms,\nlecture halls, auditoriums, laboratories, offices, staff rooms, special rooms,\nrooftop, common staircase / landings / steps / common areas, toilets, external\ncompound and handrails. </p><p>iii. During each Environmental Quality Audit,\nrepresentatives from the appointed Integrated Facilities Management Company\n(“IFMC”) shall be present. </p><p>iv. To validate that the appointed IFMC cleaning and\ndisinfection standards are in compliance with the ES Programme as mandated by\nNEA for all sites; and </p><p>v. To validate that all documentations (eg. Indoor Air\nQuality (“IAQ\") report, Comprehensive Pest Control Survey etc) required\nfor NEA ES Programme submissions are in order. </p><p>*Requirement* :<br />\nPossess valid Environmental Control Coordinator (“ECC”) license. <br />\nPossess WSQ Advanced Certificate in Environmental Cleaning/Services for\ncleaning supervisor or possess a relevant WSQ Qualification or equivalent in\ncleaning supervision </p>",
